Global setup:
 Download and install Git
  git config --global user.name "Your Name"
  git config --global user.email email@address
        
Next steps:
  mkdir Android_apps
  cd Android_apps
  git init
  touch README
  git add README
  git commit -m 'first commit'
  git remote add origin git@github.com:jy10d/Android_apps.git
  git push -u origin master
      
Existing Git Repo?
  cd existing_git_repo
  git remote add origin git@github.com:jy10d/Android_apps.git
  git push -u origin master
      
Importing a Subversion Repo?
  Click here
      
When you're done:
  Continue

To change branch in your local machine:
git branch branch_name
git checkout branch_name

upload:

git add.
git commit -m "Text_you_describe"
git push